Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Panama. All commercial flights have now ceased operation to/from Panama until at least 22 May 2020. The last airline-operated special flights have now departed.
Special European flight
A special European flight, operated by Evelop Air, will depart Panama Tocumen International Airport on Monday 11 May at 2:00 PM for Paris, France (CDG). It will make a brief stopover of 1.5hrs in Honduras (San Pedro Sula) to pick up other passengers. Passengers that have boarded the flight in Panama will not be allowed to disembark the plane in Honduras. Arrival to Paris CDG is scheduled for 10:30 AM Tuesday 12 May.
This flight is organised within the European Civil Protection Mechanism Framework and coordinated by the French Embassy, with the support of all European Embassies in Panama, the EU delegation, and the Government of Panama. The flight is reserved for European and UK tourists. In addition, European citizens residing in Panama or citizens of third states residing in the European Union who have an emergency reason to return to Europe may register their interest for the flight.
We are not aware of any other special humanitarian flights leaving from Panama City to mainland Europe and there are unlikely to be any more until the air embargo is lifted. There are no plans currently for direct flights to the UK.
How to register for the flight
If you wish to travel, you should use the form to register your interest as soon as possible. It is one form per person, including minors.
This form is not a confirmed booking for the flight. You will receive within a few days an email to confirm booking and instructions for payment.
The cost for this flight is set at €450 euros per person (there are no special fees for children).
The ticket price includes one check-in luggage of up to 23kg and one carry-on bag of up to 5kg.
If you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact: Phone: +507 297-6550, Email: Panama.Consulate@fco.gov.uk.
If you decide to book with Evelop Air, send us: * your booking confirmation * your contact telephone * your current location.
You should wear a mask, gloves and bring hand sanitiser on the trip.
Transport to the Airport
Passengers are responsible for coordinating travel to the airport. Taxis, Cabify and InDriver continue to operate, as do the two transport options below. Others may be available. You should book in advance and inform us of your arrangements, as below:
